-----
run the alpha example:
$ sudo pip install bitstring bson # optional
$ cd tweetfs
$ python payload.py
$ rm -r baz

-----
spec:
read directory:
1) pull payload from seqtweet: give url or ID (which gets turned into url)
2) unpickle that payload, expect a directory
3) switch on the object's 'type' key:
   'file' =>
            'bin'  => file contents
            'name' => filename in this dir
   'dir'  =>
            'name' => name of dir (in cwd)
            'files' => [id, id, ...]
